# Agent memory (MCP)

> **Authoritative source:** [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md#agent-memory-mcp) at repo root.
> This file duplicates critical content for Cursor compatibility.

Persistent memory via **agentmemory** MCP server (`memory_recall`, `memory_save`, etc.).
Daemon runs at `http://127.0.0.1:3111`.

## Session start (non-trivial work)

Before planning or implementing, call **`memory_recall`** with a short query (project name,
feature area, files, or keywords from the user message). Use returned context; do not re-ask
for preferences or decisions already stored.

## During work

When you learn something durable (architecture choice, convention, command to run, user
preference, gotcha), call **`memory_save`** with a concise title and content. Prefer facts
the next session would need without re-reading the repo.

## Session end

If the session produced new durable knowledge not yet saved, call **`memory_save`** once more
before finishing.

## Scope

- Project: **sapie** (knowledge-management monorepo).
- Do not store secrets (API keys, tokens, passwords).
